<sop id="DLM1460900" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" xml:lang="en-NZ" year.imprint="2008" date.terminated="2008-07-30" terminated="superseded" pco.suffix="0005" stage="published" year="2008" raised.by="Members" sop.no="221">
  <date>Wednesday, 30 July 2008</date>
  <billref>Waste Minimisation Bill</billref>
  <body id="DLM1460901">
    <heading>Proposed amendment to spending of levy money by territorial authorities</heading>
    <motion>Nicky Wagner, in Committee, to move the following amendment:</motion>
    <sop.amend id="DLM1460902">
      <clause.ref>Clause 30</clause.ref>
      <sop.para>
        <text>To omit clause 30 and substitute the following:</text>
        <instrument.amend close.quote="no" open.quote="no">
          <prov id="DLM1460903" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">30</label>
            <heading>	Spending levy money by territorial authorities</heading>
            <prov.body>
              <subprov skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
                <para>
                  <text>A territorial authority may spend the levy money it receives under <changeable>section 29 </changeable> onlyâ€”</text>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>on matters to promote or achieve waste minimisation; and</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                  <label-para skeleton="no">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                    <para>
                      <text>in accordance with its waste management and minimisation plan.</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                </para>
              </subprov>
              <subprov skeleton="no">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
                <para>
                  <text>In funding waste services through the waste levy, a territorial authority must treat private enterprise, council-controlled organisations and their own in-house operations on an equal basis.</text>
                </para>
              </subprov>
            </prov.body>
          </prov>
        </instrument.amend>
      </sop.para>
    </sop.amend>
  </body>
  <explnote id="DLM1460904" in.amend="false" irdnumbering="no" rule-after="yes" rule-before="yes" date.terminated="2008-07-30" pco.suffix="0005" stage="published" year="2008" raised.by="Members" sop.no="221">
    <heading>Explanatory note</heading>
    <para>
      <text>This Supplementary Order Paper amends the Waste Minimisation Bill. The proposed amendment requires territorial authorities to treat all organisations providing waste services equally.</text>
    </para>
  </explnote>
</sop>
